            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Keeping italic on lower priority group while removing it on a higher priority group or a more specific group would be useful. \nI am currently creating a color scheme and `:Inspect` returns this:\n\n<pre><code>Treesitter\n  - @comment.lua links to LanguageDefaults_Comments_LineComment lua\n  - @spell.lua links to @spell lua\n  - <em>@comment.documentation.lua</em> links to <em>@comment.documentation.lua_Custom</em> lua\n\nSemantic Tokens\n  - @lsp.type.keyword.lua links to LanguageDefaults_Keyword priority: 125\n  - @lsp.mod.documentation.lua links to Lua_Comments_EmmyDoc_Tag priority: 126\n  - @lsp.typemod.keyword.documentation.lua links to @lsp.typemod.keyword.documentation.lua_Custom priority: 127\n</code></pre>\n\nI am styling a documentation comment and I want `@comment.documentation.lua` to italicize the text but `@lsp.typemod.keyword.documentation.lua` to make it normal so that I have italicized text while any keyword is having normal style within the doc comment.",
