            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I don't think so; this issue is about how multiple extmarks interact, not with individual highlight groups.\n\n**EDIT:** No it doesn't (unsurprisingly); I just tested to make sure.\n\nTo be clear, the ask here is for a variant of `italic = false` that is _not_ equivalent to not setting `italic` at all. I think the simplest solution would be to add a new attribute `upright` or `normal` that if set to `true` overrides  `italic` (and possibly `bold` and `underlined` etc. -- I don't think we need a `nofoo` variant for every attribute...)",
