        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "This would also come in handy for text where both `DiagnosticDeprecated` and `DiagnosticUnderlineHint` are applied. One adds a strike-through and the other an underline. Both is visually noisy - just the strike-through would be enough.\n\n```\nExtmarks\n  - DiagnosticDeprecated nvim.nvim.lsp.intelephense.1.diagnostic.underline\n  - DiagnosticUnderlineHint nvim.nvim.lsp.intelephense.1.diagnostic.underline\n\n\nDiagnosticDeprecated xxx cterm=strikethrough gui=strikethrough guisp=NvimLightRed\nDiagnosticUnderlineHint xxx cterm=underline gui=underline guisp=NvimLightBlue\n```\n\nIn other words just adding `upright` or `normal` would not fix this.",
            "created_at": "2026-05-04T12:32:47Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/16481#issuecomment-4371062516",
